Mô Tả Công Việc


              Are You Looking For a Fun Place to Work?

              Join The Game!


              Leader in the development and publishing of mobile games, Gameloft® has established itself as one of the top innovators in its field since 2000. Gameloft creates games for all digital platforms and with an audience of 113 million monthly users offers via Gameloft Advertising Solutions a unique level of visibility and involvement to advertisers.


              Gameloft operates its own established franchises such as Asphalt®, Order & Chaos, Modern Combat and Dungeon Hunter and also partners with major rights holders including Universal, Illumination Entertainment, Disney®, Marvel®, Hasbro®, Fox Digital Entertainment, Mattel® and Ferrari®. Gameloft distributes its games in over 100 countries and employs 6,000 people worldwide. Gameloft is a Vivendi company.


              Gameloft is seeking a Graphic Designer to join our team at the head office of the group of studios in Southeast Asia - SEA  (Vietnam, Indonesia, and Philippines).


              As part of the SEA Communication team composed of young, dynamic and creative fellows, based in Ho Chi Minh City, you will create the best designs for our rich program of activities throughout the year, as well as for different actions of our employer & corporate branding.


              This position will challenge your skills against varied types and formats of communication (either online or offline), thus constantly help develop and enrich your design expertise and creativity.


              You will be responsible for the following main tasks:

              - Create concepts, develop design materials following design briefs, for either online or offline communication platforms;

              - Discuss, advise manager in concept, and art direction for various design requests; present finalized options to manager and stakeholders;

              - Actively follow up the design works with related stakeholders, to ensure on-time delivery and highest quality;

              - Actively research on innovative design approaches and ideas, to improve efficiency and creativity;

              - Create artworks, visual elements and guidelines in collaboration with related communication specialists;

              - Organize, build database of design assets.


              Xem toàn bộ Mô Tả Công Việc

requirement:
Yêu Cầu Công Việc


              The ideal candidate should demonstrate the following skill set:


              - Expertise in graphic design, UI/UX;

              - Good command of design tools (Photoshop, Illustrator…);

              - Strong creativity; curiosity and eagerness to learn, research on design/culture matters;

              - Good aesthetic sense, and high demanding for quality;

              - Good English (writing and speaking);


